# Git & Pull Request Guidelines

## Pull Request Format
When creating pull requests:
- Use conventional commits style for titles: `type: description`
  - `feat:` new feature
  - `fix:` bug fix
  - `docs:` documentation changes
  - `chore:` maintenance tasks
  - `refactor:` code refactoring
  - `test:` adding or updating tests
  - `ci:` CI/CD changes
- Do NOT include a "Test plan" section
- Do NOT include AI/Cursor attribution
- Keep the summary concise with bullet points

## Commit Messages
- Use conventional commits style: `type: description`
- Keep the first line under 72 characters
- Use lowercase for the description (e.g., `feat: add user auth` not `feat: Add user auth`)
